“The sea is ours”: the coastless country of Bolivia hopes that the court will reopen the way to the Pacific Ocean
The sails guard the naval headquarters in La Paz.
General buildings of the blue flag.
Floating stations from Titicaca Lake to the Amazon River are marked with the slogan: “We have the right to the sea.
