Nelson Mandela said, “If you speak to a man in a language he understands, it touches his mind.
If you speak to him in his native language, it touches his heart.”
This is an important reminder that we can’t just rely on English to build relationships and trust with people from other countries.
This year’s test results show us that languages are at the top of the lists with the highest proportion of students passing exams in private schools.
68 per cent of foreign language learners received the grade A.
The data, collected from 74 schools within the SCIS, showed that 72 percent of students received the excellence grade A in mandarin, while 72 percent of those who learned German, 69 percent of those who learned French, and 63 percent of those who learned Spanish also received the excellence grade A.
