Multilingualism, especially in new markets, will give children a better opportunity to find meaningful jobs.
In Scotland, there is a difference between schools in what language they teach.
A certain number of schools will focus on more classical new languages, while others will teach languages that are considered to be most important to the UK when looking ahead to 2020, such as Mandarin or Japanese.
No matter where your child’s interest lies, they will always be able to choose from languages in private schools with specially trained teachers.
Scottish private schools are committed to providing a learning environment that will prepare children and equip them with the skills they need to succeed, no matter what the future holds.
It cannot be denied that at this time, in a global business environment, languages continue to be essential for the future of the country, and it must be reflected in education.
In fact, modern languages should really be viewed as “international skills in communication.”
Private schools will continue to offer choice, diversity and superiority for Scotland’s young people.
I'm fine with the fair.
